  ==
  - Williams' 齋戒: Properly, abstinence from all pleasures (meat, alcohol, sex).
  - Williams' 齋醮: Corrected _tsi(u/)(6)_ [[ziu6]] to _tsi(u/)(3)_ [[ziu3]].
  - Williams' 羅漢齋: The name of a dish, commonly called Buddha's Delight.
  ==
E
  ====
  - 【齋】 (zaai1):
    ++
    1. Vegetarian food.
       ==
       - 初一十五食齋 (co1 jat1 sap6 ng5 sik6 zaai1):
         "Eating vegetarian [on the] first [and] fifteenth [of the lunar month]."
       - 齋口唔齋心 (zaai1 hau2 m4 zaai1 sam1):
         "Vegetarian [in] mouth [but] not vegetarian [at] heart"
         (said of vegetarians that eat imitation meat).
       ==
    1. Plain, pure, etc.
       ==
       - 齋啡 (zaai1 fe1): "Straight coffee."
       - 齋腸 (zaai1 coeng4-2): "Plain [rice-noodle] roll."
       - 齋噏 (zaai1 ngap1): "Purely blabbering."
       ==
    ++
  - 【話齋】 (waa6 zaai1):
    ++
    1. Emphatic form of "[as he] said".
      ==
      - 好似佢話齋 (hou2 ci5 keoi5 waa6 zaai1): "As he said."
      ==
    ++
